      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The legal and ethical framework of a modern, democratic state must prioritize secular law and equal protection for all citizens. While religious freedom is a fundamental right, it is not absolute and cannot supersede the laws designed to protect public safety and the rights of every individual. The \"correct\" approach is to maintain a separation of church and state, ensuring that religious beliefs do not grant exemptions from universal legal obligations.",
